{
  "texts": [
    "The agreement in this article is that the experimental results of sentence pairs that meet the constraints are valid.",
    "If the experimental results do not meet the constraints, they are considered invalid and require recalculation.",
    "We change the inequality constraints to two constraint functions.f i (x) = x i -(1 + λ)y i, (16)andg i (x) = (1 -λ)y i -x i.",
    "(17)λ is set as the regulating parameter of constraint functions.",
    "f i (x) and g i (x) are determined by λ and x i, because the annotated value y i of each sentence pair is a constant.To minimize the recalculation of the constraint function values for sentence pairs, the model can be optimized through two primary approaches: tuning the parameter λ and reducing sentence dimensions to achieve alignment between x i and y i."
  ]
}